        [[Delete]] (P) When the [[Delete]] method of O is called with property name P, the following steps are taken:
        1. If O doesn’t have a property with name P, return true.
        2. If the property has the DontDelete attribute, return false.
        3. Remove the property with name P from O.
        4. Return true.

      • baseGetOwnProperty

        public BaseProperty baseGetOwnProperty(BasePrimitiveString name)
        Description copied from interface: BaseObject
        8.6.2.1.2 [[GetOwnProperty]] (P)

        When the [[GetOwnProperty]] method of O is called with property name P, the following steps are taken:
        1. If Type(O) is String, and Type(P) is Number, go to step 4.
        2. If O is an instance of String, and Type(P) is a Number, go to step 4.
        3. Go to step 6.
        4. Call the [[Call]] method of the specified String.prototype.charAt method with O as the this value and argument P.
        5. Return a DDesc describing Result(4).
        6. If O doesn‘t have an own property with name P, return undefined.
        7. If O has an own data property with name P, return a DDesc describing its current state
        8. If O has an own procedural property with name P, return a PDesc describing its current state.

        Specified by:
        baseGetOwnProperty in interface BaseObject
        Parameters:
        name - TODO change to BasePrimitive or CharSequence and int
        Returns:
